  "prompt": "How do I make reading my hobby?",
  "response": "Here are some tips to help make reading a hobby:\n\n1. Find your interests\n- Choose books in genres you enjoy\n- Read about topics that fascinate you\n- Try different styles of writing\n\n2. Start small\n- Begin with shorter books\n- Set achievable reading goals\n- Read for 15-30 minutes daily\n\n3. Create a comfortable reading environment\n- Find a cozy reading spot\n- Minimize distractions\n- Use good lighting\n\n4. Explore different formats\n- Physical books\n- E-books\n- Audiobooks\n- Magazines\n- Graphic novels\n\n5. Join reading communities\n- Book clubs\n- Online reading forums\n- Goodreads\n- Reddit reading groups\n\n6. Make it convenient\n- Always have a book with you\n- Use reading apps\n- Download books on your phone/tablet\n\n7. Track your progress\n- Use reading apps to log books\n- Set yearly reading challenges\n- Reward yourself for reaching goals\n\n8. Mix up your reading material\n- Fiction and non-fiction\n- Classics and contemporary works\n- Different genres\n\n9. Reduce digital distractions\n- Limit screen time\n- Put phone on silent while reading\n- Create dedicated reading time\n\n10. Be patient with yourself\n- Don't force reading\n- Enjoy the process\n- Switch books if you're not enjoying one",
